# An example of running the NooneCurves.py program with additional
# setting given in the command line.
# Here the variable delp is set to -10, the plot_file name is set to be
# "Plot_delp_-10.pdf". Note that the \" is required to delineate the
# file name so the Bash shell does not remove any quotes for the file
# name text string.
# Once these two parameters have been set explicitly, the files et_parms
# is read to set any parameter values.

NooneCurves.py delp=-10 plot_file=\"Plot_delp_-10.pdf\" set_parms
